annotationA: GDP-fucose transporter 1; Involved in GDP-fucose import from the cytoplasm into the Golgi lumen. Plays a major role in the fucosylation of N- glycans. Functions redundantly with Efr in the O-fucosylation of Notch, positively regulating Notch signaling
annotationB: EG:100G10.5 protein; Sugar:proton symporter activity; UDP-galactose transmembrane transporter activity; UDP-N-acetylgalactosamine transmembrane transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: UDP-galactose transport; UDP-N-acetylgalactosamine transport; galactose transport
